25 factors" to the payroll data, properly classified for the purpose of
26 computing the reserve liability of the trust fund as of the end of
27 the fiscal year.
28 SCHEDULE V. The application of actuarially computed "current
29 liability factors" to the payroll data, properly classified for the
30 purpose of computing the liability of the trust fund for the end of
31 the fiscal year.
32 SCHEDULE VI. An actuarial computation of the pension liability
33 for all employees retired before the close of the fiscal year.
34 (i) The minimum annual contribution by the department must be of
35 sufficient amount, as determined by the pension consultants, to prevent
36 any deterioration in the actuarial status of the pension plan during that
