1 (29) "Tangible net worth" means the aggregate assets of a
2 licensee, excluding all intangible assets, less liabilities, as
3 determined in accordance with United States generally accepted
4 accounting principles.
5 SECTION 21. IC 33-38-6-23, AS AMENDED BY P.L.35-2012,
6 SECTION 103, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
7 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 23. (a) The board of trustees of the
8 Indiana public retirement system (referred to as "the system" in this
9 section) shall administer the fund, which may be commingled for
10 investment purposes with any public pension and retirement fund
11 administered by the system.
12 (b) The board shall do the following:
13 (1) Determine eligibility for and make payments of benefits under
14 IC 33-38-7 and IC 33-38-8.
15 (2) In accordance with the powers and duties granted it in
16 IC 5-10.3-3-7.1, IC 5-10.3-5-3 through IC 5-10.3-5-6,
17 IC 5-10.5-4, and IC 5-10.5-6, administer the fund.
18 (3) Provide by rule for the implementation of this chapter and
19 IC 33-38-7 and IC 33-38-8.
20 (4) Authorize deposits.
21 (c) A determination by the board may be appealed under the
22 procedures in IC 4-21.5.
23 (d) The powers and duties of:
24 (1) the director and the actuary of the board; and
25 (2) the attorney general;
26 with respect to the fund are those specified in IC 5-10.3-3, IC 5-10.3-4,
27 IC 5-10.5-4, and IC 5-10.5-6.
28 (e) The board may hire additional personnel, including hearing
29 officers, to assist it in the implementation of this chapter.
30 (f) Fund records of individual participants and participants'
31 information are confidential, except for the name and years of service
32 of a fund participant.
33 (g) The board may invest the assets of the fund in
34 cryptocurrency exchange traded funds.
